HEADWORD: Meuse-Argonne
<hw>Meuse-Argonne</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>an American operation in
World War I (1918); American troops under Pershing drove back the German
armies which were saved only by the Armistice on November 11.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Meuse, Meuse River, Argonne, Argonne Forest,
Meuse-Argonne operation.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

